        "body": "Nobody plans to be broke at 30. But most people don't plan NOT to be — and that's usually enough.\n\nA financial roadmap is just decisions made early: what you want, what it costs, and when you want it. It covers the expected (a car, a degree) and cushions the unexpected (a lost job, a medical bill).\n\nWith a plan, you stop reacting to money problems and start steering toward goals. Same income — totally different trajectory.",
